C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F22182949%2F1024px-Tear_Gas_outside_United_States_Capitol_20210106.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F22182949%2F1024px-Tear_Gas_outside_United_States_Capitol_20210106.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F22182949%2F1024px-Tear_Gas_outside_United_States_Capitol_20210106-300x155.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669218%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22528%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%20supporters%20storm%20the%20US%20Capitol%20on%20January%206%2C%202021.%20Photo%3A%20Tyler%20Merbler%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Finvestigates%2Fspecial-report%2Fusa-politics-violence%2F%5C%22%3EMonitoring%20by%20the%20Reuters%20news%20agency%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20identified%20almost%2040%20politically-motivated%20killings%20in%20the%20USA%20since%20January%206%2C%202021.%20There%20were%20213%20documented%20cases%20of%20political%20violence%20in%20the%20same%20period.%20Most%20(two-thirds)%20were%20by%20lone%20assailants%20or%20carried%20out%20during%20clashes%20between%20opposing%20groups%20at%20public%20rallies%20or%20protests.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E2016%20%E2%80%93%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20ultimately%20victorious%20election%20campaign%20%E2%80%93%20marks%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20recent%20resurgence%20of%20political%20violence.%20According%20to%20academic%20researchers%20such%20as%20Professor%20Gary%20LaFree%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Maryland%2C%20political%20violence%20is%20still%20trending%20upward%20and%20has%20yet%20to%20plateau%20%E2%80%93%20let%20alone%20decline.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20hostile%20environment%20for%20election%20officials%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20important%20academic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.journalofdemocracy.org%2Farticles%2Fthe-rise-of-political-violence-in-the-united-states%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJournal%20of%20Democracy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20pointed%20out%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20problem%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAn%20unprecedented%20number%20of%20elections%20administrators%20received%20threats%20in%202020%E2%80%94so%20much%20so%20that%20a%20third%20of%20poll%20workers%20surveyed%20by%20the%20Brennan%20Center%20for%20Justice%20in%20April%202021%20said%20that%20they%20felt%20unsafe%20and%2079%25%20wanted%20government-provided%20security.%20In%20July%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20set%20up%20a%20special%20task%20force%20specifically%20to%20combat%20threats%20against%20election%20administrators.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20that%20article%2C%20Rachel%20Kleinfeld%20argues%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20bedrock%20idea%20uniting%20right-wing%20communities%20who%20condone%20violence%20is%20that%20white%20Christian%20men%20in%20the%20United%20States%20are%20under%20cultural%20and%20demographic%20threat%20and%20require%20defending%E2%80%94and%20that%20it%20is%20the%20Republican%20Party%20and%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20who%20will%20safeguard%20their%20way%20of%20life%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20Kleinfeld%2C%20four%20factors%20elevate%20the%20risk%20of%20election-related%20violence.%20%E2%80%9C1)%20a%20highly%20competitive%20election%20that%20could%20shift%20the%20balance%20of%20power%3B%202)%20partisan%20division%20based%20on%20identity%3B%203)%20electoral%20rules%20that%20enable%20winning%20by%20exploiting%20identity%20cleavages%3B%20and%204)%20weak%20institutional%20constraints%20on%20violence%2C%20particularly%20security-sector%20bias%20toward%20one%20group%2C%20leading%20perpetrators%20to%20believe%20they%20will%20not%20be%20held%20accountable%20for%20violence%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20of%20the%20above%20are%20present%20in%20spades%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20the%20politics%20of%20the%20GOP%2C%20led%20by%20the%20inflammatory%20leading%20Republican%20Trump%2C%20who%20is%20adding%20fuel%20to%20the%20fire%20on%20a%20frequent%20and%20regular%20basis.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ETrumpism%20is%20gangsterism%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERecently%2C%20after%20being%20indicted%20for%20aspects%20of%20the%20January%206%20attacks%2C%20Trump%20threatened%20on%20his%20social%20media%20platform%20Truth%20Social%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20go%20after%20me%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20coming%20after%20you!%E2%80%9D%20This%20was%20interpreted%20by%20prosecutors%20and%20the%20presiding%20judge%2C%20Tanya%20Chutkan%2C%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20threaten%20potential%20witnesses%20in%20the%20upcoming%20trial.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20thinly%20veiled%20racist%20swipe%20against%20African-Americans%20living%20in%20Washington%20D.C.%2C%20Trump%20wrote%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9CNO%20WAY%E2%80%9D%20he%20could%20get%20a%20fair%20trial%20in%20D.C.%20a%20%E2%80%9CFILTHY%20AND%20CRIME%20RIDDEN%20EMBARRASSMENT%20TO%20OUR%20NATION.%E2%80%9D%20Trump%20called%20for%20Judge%20Chutkan%2C%20an%20African-American%2C%20to%20recuse%20herself%20and%20for%20the%20trial%20to%20be%20moved%20outside%20of%20Washington%20D.C.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20statement%20echoed%20his%20notoriously%20racist%20references%20to%20Haiti%20and%20African%20countries%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fpolitics%2Fwhite-house%2Ftrump-referred-haiti-african-countries-shithole-nations-n836946%5C%22%3Eshitholes%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20in%202018%2C%20during%20his%20presidency.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20numerous%20Sunday%20morning%20TV%20talk%20shows%2C%20Trum