pUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22World's%20Space%20Agencies%20Are%20Racing%20To%20Moon's%20South%20Pole.%20Here's%20Why%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia's%20space%20agency%20is%20attempting%20to%20land%20a%20spacecraft%20on%20the%20moon's%20south%20pole%2C%20a%20mission%20that%20could%20advance%20India's%20space%20ambitions%20and%20expand%20knowledge%20of%20lunar%20water%20ice%2C%20potentially%20one%20of%20the%20moon's%20most%20valuable%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere's%20what's%20known%20about%20the%20presence%20of%20frozen%20water%20on%20the%20moon%20-%20and%20why%20space%20agencies%20and%20private%20companies%20see%20it%20as%20a%20key%20to%20a%20moon%20colony%2C%20lunar%20mining%20and%20potential%20missions%20to%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHOW%20DID%20SCIENTISTS%20FIND%20WATER%20ON%20THE%20MOON%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20early%20as%20the%201960s%2C%20before%20the%20first%20Apollo%20landing%2C%20scientists%20had%20speculated%20that%20water%20could%20exist%20on%20the%20moon.%20Samples%20the%20Apollo%20crews%20returned%20for%20analysis%20in%20the%20late%201960s%20and%20early%201970s%20appeared%20to%20be%20dry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202008%2C%20Brown%20University%20researchers%20revisited%20those%20lunar%20samples%20with%20new%20technology%20and%20found%20hydrogen%20inside%20tiny%20beads%20of%20volcanic%20glass.%20In%202009%2C%20a%20NASA%20instrument%20aboard%20the%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation's%20Chandrayaan-1%20probe%20detected%20water%20on%20the%20moon's%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20year%2C%20another%20NASA%20probe%20that%20hit%20the%20south%20pole%20found%20water%20ice%20below%20the%20moon's%20surface.%20An%20earlier%20NASA%20mission%2C%20the%201998%20Lunar%20Prospector%2C%20had%20found%20evidence%20that%20the%20highest%20concentration%20of%20water%20ice%20was%20in%20the%20south%20pole's%20shadowed%20craters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWHY%20IS%20WATER%20ON%20THE%20MOON%20IMPORTANT%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20are%20interested%20in%20pockets%20of%20ancient%20water%20ice%20because%20they%20could%20provide%20a%20record%20of%20lunar%20volcanoes%2C%20material%20that%20comets%20and%20asteroids%20delivered%20to%20Earth%2C%20and%20the%20origin%20of%20oceans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20water%20ice%20exists%20in%20sufficient%20quantities%2C%20it%20could%20be%20a%20source%20of%20drinking%20water%20for%20moon%20exploration%20and%20could%20help%20cool%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20also%20be%20broken%20down%20to%20produce%20hydrogen%20for%20fuel%20and%20oxygen%20to%20breathe%2C%20supporting%20missions%20to%20Mars%20or%20lunar%20mining.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%201967%20United%20Nations%20Outer%20Space%20Treaty%20prohibits%20any%20nation%20from%20claiming%20ownership%20of%20the%20moon.%20There%20is%20no%20provision%20that%20would%20stop%20commercial%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20U.S.-led%20effort%20to%20establish%20a%20set%20of%20principles%20for%20moon%20exploration%20and%20the%20use%20of%20its%20resources%2C%20the%20Artemis%20Accords%2C%20has%2027%20signatories.%20China%20and%20Russia%20have%20not%20signed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWHAT%20MAKES%20THE%20SOUTH%20POLE%20ESPECIALLY%20TRICKY%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAttempted%20landings%20on%20the%20moon%20have%20failed%20before.%20Russia's%20Luna-25%20craft%20had%20been%20scheduled%20to%20land%20on%20the%20south%20pole%20this%20week%20but%20spun%20out%20of%20control%20on%20approach%20and%20crashed%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20south%20pole%20-%20far%20from%20the%20equatorial%20region%20targeted%20by%20previous%20missions%2C%20including%20the%20crewed%20Apollo%20landings%20-%20is%20full%20of%20craters%20and%20deep%20trenches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EISRO's%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%20is%20on%20track%20for%20an%20attempted%20landing%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20space%20agency%20has%20said.%20A%20previous%20Indian%20mission%20failed%20in%202019%20to%20safely%20land%20near%20the%20area%20targeted%20by%20Chandrayaan-3.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20United%20States%20and%20China%20have%20planned%20missions%20to%20the%20south%20pole.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692755940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fogfro2dg_luna-25-mission_625x300_19_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fspace-agencies-around-the-world-are-racing-to-moons-south-pole-heres-why-4320937%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20space%20agency%20is%20attempting%20to%20land%20a%20spacecraft%20on%20the%20moon's%20south%20pole%2C%20a%20mission%20that%20could%20advance%20India's%20space%20ambitions%20and%20expand%20knowledge%20of%20lunar%20water%20ice%2C%20potentially%20one%20of%20the%20moon's%20most%20valuable%20resources.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fspace-agencies-around-the-world-are-racing-to-moons-south-pole-heres-why-4320937%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fspace-agencies-around-the-world-are-racing-to-moons-south-pole-heres-why-4320937%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fspace-agencies-around-the-world-are-racing-to-moons-south-pole-heres-why-4320937%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Market%20LIVE%3A%20Wall%20Street%20muted%20on%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%20rating%20downgrade%3B%20Asia%20mixed%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692755890000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-08%2F07%2Ffull%2F1691380420-4084.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-live-august-23-nse-bse-sensex-today-nifty-rupee-us-yields-share-market-updates-123082300067_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stock%20market%20LIVE%20updates%3A%20At%206%3A55%20am%2C%20the%20Gift%20Nifty%20Futures%20declined%2037-odd%20points%20to%20trade%20around%2019%2C349%20levels%20over%20Nifty%20Futures'%20Tuesday%20close%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-live-august-23-nse-bse-sensex-today-nifty-rupee-us-yields-share-market-updates-123082300067_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-live-august-23-nse-bse-sensex-today-nifty-rupee-us-yields-share-market-updates-123082300067_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-live-august-23-nse-bse-sensex-today-nifty-rupee-us-yields-share-market-updates-123082300067_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India's%20Boom%2C%20Russia's%20Crunch%3A%20How%20Money%20Is%20Shaping%20A%20New%20Space%20Race%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20space%20race%20India%20aims%20to%20win%20this%20week%20by%20landing%20first%20on%20the%20moon's%20south%20pole%20is%20about%20science%2C%20the%20politics%20of%20national%20prestige%20and%20a%20new%20frontier%3A%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20Chandrayaan-3%20is%20heading%20for%20a%20landing%20on%20the%20lunar%20south%20pole%20on%20Wednesday.%20If%20it%20succeeds%2C%20analysts%20and%20executives%20expect%20an%20immediate%20boost%20for%20the%20South%20Asian%20nation's%20nascent%20space%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia's%20Luna-25%2C%20which%20launched%20less%20than%20two%20weeks%20ago%2C%20had%20been%20on%20track%20to%20get%20there%20first%20-%20before%20the%20lander%20crashed%20from%20orbit%2C%20possibly%20taking%20with%20it%20the%20funding%20for%20a%20successor%20mission%2C%20analysts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20seemingly%20sudden%20competition%20to%20get%20to%20a%20previously%20unexplored%20region%20of%20the%20moon%20recalls%20the%20space%20race%20of%20the%201960s%2C%20when%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20competed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20now%20space%20is%20a%20business%2C%20and%20the%20moon's%20south%20pole%20is%20a%20prize%20because%20of%20the%20water%20ice%20there%20that%20planners%20expect%20could%20support%20a%20future%20lunar%20colony%2C%20mining%20operations%20and%20eventual%20missions%20to%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20push%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20India%20has%20privatised%20space%20launches%20and%20is%20looking%20to%20open%20the%20sector%20to%20foreign%20investment%20as%20it%20targets%20a%20five-fold%20increase%20in%20its%20share%20of%20the%20global%20launch%20market%20within%20the%20next%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Chandrayaan-3%20succeeds%2C%20analysts%20expect%20India's%20space%20sector%20to%20capitalise%20on%20a%20reputation%20for%20cost-competitive%20engineering.%20The%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)%20had%20a%20budget%20of%20around%20just%20%2474%20million%20for%20the%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20is%20on%20track%20to%20spend%20roughly%20%2493%20billion%20on%20its%20Artemis%20moon%20programme%20through%202025%2C%20the%20U.S.%20space%20agency's%20inspector%20general%20has%20estimated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20moment%20this%20mission%20is%20successful%2C%20it%20raises%20the%20profile%20of%20everyone%20associated%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ajey%20Lele%2C%20a%20consultant%20at%20New%20Delhi's%20Manohar%20Parrikar%20Institute%20for%20Defence%20Studies%20and%20Analyses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20world%20looks%20at%20a%20mission%20like%20this%2C%20they%20aren't%20looking%20at%20ISRO%20in%20isolation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERUSSIA'S%20CRUNCH%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20Western%20sanctions%20over%20its%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20increasing%20isolation%2C%20Russia%20managed%20to%20launch%20a%20moonshot.%20But%20some%20experts%20doubt%20its%20ability%20to%20fund%20a%20successor%20to%20Luna-25.%20Russia%20has%20not%20disclosed%20what%20it%20spent%20on%20the%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExpenses%20for%20space%20exploration%20are%20systematically%20reduced%20from%20year%20to%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Vadim%20Lukashevich%2C%20an%20independent%20space%20expert%20and%20author%20based%20in%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia's%20budget%20prioritisation%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20makes%20a%20repeat%20of%20Luna-25%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20unlikely%26quot%3B%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20had%20been%20considering%20a%20role%20in%20NASA's%20Artemis%20programme%20until%202021%2C%20when%20it%20said%20it%20would%20partner%20instead%20on%20China's%20moon%20programme.%20Few%20details%20of%20that%20effort%20have%20been%20disclosed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20made%20the%20first%20ever%20soft%20landing%20on%20the%20far%20side%20of%20the%20moon%20in%202019%20and%20has%20more%20missions%20planned.%20Space%20research%20firm%20Euroconsult%20estimates%20China%20spent%20%2412%20billion%20on%20its%20space%20programme%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENASA'S%20PLAYBOOK%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20by%20opening%20to%20private%20money%2C%20NASA%20has%20provided%20the%20playbook%20India%20is%20following%2C%20officials%20there%20have%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElon%20Musk's%20SpaceX%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20developing%20the%20Starship%20rocket%20for%20its%20satellite%20launch%20business%20as%20well%20as%20to%20ferry%20NASA%20astronauts%20to%20the%20moon's%20surface%20under%20a%20%243-billion%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20that%20contract%2C%20SpaceX%20will%20spend%20roughly%20%242%20billion%20on%20Starship%20this%20year%2C%20Musk%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EU.S.%20space%20firms%20Astrobotic%20and%20Intuitive%20Machines%20are%20building%20lunar%20landers%20that%20are%20expected%20to%20launch%20to%20the%20moon's%20south%20pole%20by%20year's%20end%2C%20or%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20companies%20such%20as%20Axiom%20Space%20and%20Jeff%20Bezos'%20Blue%20Origin%20are%20developing%20privately%20funded%20successors%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%20On%20Monday%2C%20Axiom%20said%20it%20raised%20%24350%20million%20from%20Saudi%20and%20South%20Korean%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpace%20remains%20risky.%20India's%20last%20attempt%20to%20land%20failed%20in%202019%2C%20the%20same%20year%20an%20Israeli%20startup%20failed%20at%20what%20would%20have%20been%20the%20first%20privately%20funded%20moon%20landing.%20Japanese%20startup%20ispace%20had%20a%20failed%20landing%20attempt%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLanding%20on%20the%20moon%20is%20hard%2C%20as%20we're%20seeing%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bethany%20Ehlmann%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20California%20Institute%20of%20Technology%2C%20who%20is%20working%20with%20NASA%20on%20a%202024%20mission%20to%20map%20the%20lunar%20south%20pole%20and%20its%20water%20ice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20the%20moon%20seems%20to%20be%20eating%20spacecraft.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692755880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fil6j2cag_chandrayaan-students-afp_625x300_23_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan-3-vs-luna-25-indias-boom-russias-crunch-how-money-is-shaping-a-new-space-race-4320932%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20space%20race%20India%20aims%20to%20win%20this%20week%20by%20landing%20first%20on%20the%20moon's%20south%20pole%20is%20about%20science%2C%20the%20politics%20of%20national%20prestige%20and%20a%20new%20frontier%3A%20money.%22%2C%22author%22%