20bubble%20at%20the%20core%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e4ec3cbd98a600197c16b8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222029%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20image%20of%20the%20Ring%20Nebula%20appears%20as%20a%20distorted%20doughnut.%20The%20nebula%E2%80%99s%20inner%20cavity%20hosts%20shades%20of%20blue%20and%20green%2C%20while%20the%20detailed%20ring%20transitions%20through%20shades%20of%20orange%20in%20the%20inner%20regions%20and%20pink%20in%20the%20outer%20region.%20The%20ring%E2%80%99s%20inner%20region%20has%20distinct%20filament%20elements.%3Cp%3EESA%2FWebb%2C%20NASA%2C%20CSA%2C%20M.%20Barlow%2C%20N.%20Cox%2C%20R.%20Wesson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20detail%20is%20hauntingly%20beautiful.%20But%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronomer-animations-reveal-solar-system-physics-2021-10%5C%22%3Eastronomer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20new%20Webb%20images%20reveal%20crucial%20clues%20that%20could%20help%20solve%20a%20mystery%20about%20nebulae.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlanetary%20nebulae%20were%20once%20thought%20to%20be%20simple%2C%20round%20objects%20with%20a%20single%20dying%20star%20at%20the%20center.%20They%20were%20named%20for%20their%20fuzzy%2C%20planet-like%20appearance%20through%20small%20telescopes%2C%26quot%3B%20Wesson%20said.%20%26quot%3BModern%20observations%2C%20though%2C%20show%20that%20most%20planetary%20nebulae%20display%20breathtaking%20complexity.%20It%20begs%20the%20question%3A%20how%20does%20a%20spherical%20star%20create%20such%20intricate%20and%20delicate%20non-spherical%20structures%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWebb%20shows%20that%20the%20answer%20may%20be%20another%20star%20hidden%20in%20the%20folds%20of%20the%20nebula.%20The%20gravity%20of%20this%20star%2C%20though%20it%20probably%20isn't%20very%20massive%2C%20would%20affect%20the%20dying%20star%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20nebula%20and%20add%20complexity%20to%20the%20physics%20of%20its%20outer%20layers%20ejecting%20into%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20findings%20are%20still%20in%20progress%20and%20have%20not%20yet%20been%20peer-reviewed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWebb's%20infrared%20photo%20shows%20telltale%20arcs%20outside%20the%20main%20ring%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221257%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22nebula%20in%20space%20with%20a%20pink%20bubble%20center%20and%20a%20textured%20orange%20ring%20surrounding%20it%20with%20wavy%20blue%20hazy%20lines%20and%20green%20arrows%20overlaid%20pointing%20to%20faint%20concentric%20arcs%20expanding%20out%20into%20space%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e4e5c1bd98a600197c0dc9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22942%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Webb%20image%20reveals%20faint%20concentric%20arcs%20beyond%20the%20nebula's%20outer%20ring.%3Cp%3EESA%2FWebb%2C%20NASA%2C%20CSA%2C%20M.%20Barlow%20(UCL)%2C%20N.%20Cox%20(ACRI-ST)%2C%20R.%20Wesson%20(Cardiff%20University)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20outer%20edges%20of%20the%20main%20ring%2C%20the%20Webb%20image%20picked%20up%20about%2010%20concentric%20arcs.%20They're%20evenly%20spaced%20and%20each%20may%20have%20formed%20every%20280%20years%20as%20the%20star%20at%20the%20center%20discarded%20its%20outer%20layers.%20But%20the%20dying%20star%20couldn't%20have%20created%20them%20on%20its%20own%2C%20scientists%20think.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20presence%20of%20the%20companion%20star%20helped%20fashion%20the%20shed%20atmosphere%20into%20the%20arcs.%20If%20confirmed%2C%20this%20companion%20star%20would%20be%C2%A0about%20the%20same%20distance%20from%20the%20dying%20star%20as%20Earth%20is%20from%20Pluto.%20%26quot%3BNo%20previous%20telescope%20had%20the%20sensitivity%20and%20the%20spatial%20resolution%20to%20uncover%20this%20subtle%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20Wesson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-james-webb