nAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fclimate-change-supercharged-fire-weather-behind-canada-blazes%2Famp_articleshow%2F102956413.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fclimate-change-supercharged-fire-weather-behind-canada-blazes%2Famp_articleshow%2F102956413.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Over%2022%2C000%20student-loan%20borrowers%20are%20getting%20%249%20million%20in%20refunds%20after%20being%20charged%20up%20to%20%24800%20in%20'illegal'%20fees%20for%20debt%20relief%20services%2C%20federal%20watchdogs%20say%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224436%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22College%20graduates%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F618abcda23745d001825b741%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223327%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECollege%20graduates.%3Cp%3ERobyn%20Beck%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20FTC%20and%20DOJ%20announced%20it%20would%20be%20sending%20%249%20million%20in%20refunds%20to%2022%2C000%20student-loan%20borrowers.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt's%20a%20result%20of%20a%20company%20that%20was%20convicted%20of%20illegally%20charging%20borrowers%20for%20debt%20relief%20services.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EImpacted%20borrowers%20will%20be%20getting%20payments%20via%20check%20or%20PayPal%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scams%20keep%20coming%20for%20student-loan%20borrowers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20federal%20watchdogs%20are%20cracking%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20and%20Department%20of%20Justice%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2023%2F08%2Fftc-doj-send-more-9-million-refunds-people-who-lost-money-student-loan-debt-relief-scheme%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20will%20be%20sending%20over%20%249%20million%20in%20refunds%20to%20student-loan%20borrowers%20who%20gave%20money%20to%20Ameritech%20Financial%2C%20which%20the%20agencies%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bstudent%20loan%20debt%20relief%20scheme%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20DOJ%20brought%20charges%20against%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecifically%2C%20the%20FTC%20first%20filed%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2018%2F02%2Fftc-charges-ameritech-brandon-frere-deceiving-consumers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomplaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202018%20accusing%20Brandon%20Frere%2C%20who%20ran%20the%20company%2C%20of%20pretending%20to%20be%20affiliated%20with%20the%20Education%20Department%20and%20charging%20borrowers%20up%20to%20%24800%20in%20%26quot%3Billegal%20up-front%20fees%26quot%3B%20for%20debt%20relief%20services.%20The%20company%20also%20told%20borrowers%20that%20their%20%2449-99%20monthly%20membership%20fees%20would%20go%20toward%20their%20student-loan%20balances%2C%20but%20that%20was%20not%20the%20case.%20The%20FTC%20in%202020%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2020%2F11%2Fstudent-loan-debt-relief-scammer-brandon-frere-agrees-settle-ftc-charges%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebanned%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20company%20from%20providing%20debt%20relief%20services%2C%20and%20the%20same%20year%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20sentenced%20Frere%20to%2042%20months%20in%20prison.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20the%20legal%20proceedings%2C%2022%2C562%20borrowers%20who%20paid%20for%20Ameritech's%20services%20will%20receive%20refund%20checks%20in%20the%20mail%2C%20and%20those%20who%20do%20not%20have%20an%20address%20on%20file%20will%20receive%20a%20payment%20via%20PayPal.%20Those%20who%20have%20questions%20about%20the%20refunds%20can%20contact%20Rust%20Consulting%2C%20which%20contracts%20with%20the%20FTC%20to%20facilitate%20payments%2C%20at%201-833-579-3126.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FTC%20wrote%20in%20its%20initial%20complaint%20that%20the%20company%20sent%20mailers%20to%20consumers%20expressing%20an%20urgency%20to%20sign%20up%20for%20debt%20relief%20services%2C%20and%20later%20pressured%20borrowers%20to%20%26quot%3Bquickly%20click%20through%20the%20document%20and%20electronically%20sign%20multiple%20pages.%20In%20some%20instances%2C%20Defendants%20represent%20that%20consumers%20do%20not%20need%20to%20read%20the%20agreement%20carefully%20because%20the%20information%20contained%20in%20the%20contract%20was%20already%20discussed%20in%20the%20call.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20calls%2C%20Defendants%20transfer%20consumers%20to%20the%20Verification%20Department%20where%20employees%20quickly%20read%20lengthy%20disclosures%20to%20consumers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScams%20have%20been%20increasingly%20scrutinized%20with%20the%20changing%20student-loan%20landscape.%20After%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20announced%20his%20broad%20debt%20relief%20plan%20nearly%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20the%20Education%20Department%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-protect-student-loan-borrowers-from-scams-relief-application-2022-10%5C%22%3Ewarned%20borrowers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20wary%20of%20any%20efforts%20that%20would%20require%20them%20to%20pay%20for%20debt%20relief%20services%2C%20given%20that%20any%20help%20with%20repayment%20is%20also%20free%20from%20the%20government.%20Most%20recently%2C%20the%20FTC%20announced%20on%20Monday%20that%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-borrowers-scammed-millions-debt-relief-fees-ftc-2023-8%5C%22%3Efederal%20court%20halted%20operations%20of%20two%20companies%20that%20misled%20borrowers%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20paying%20for%20debt%20relief%20services%2C%20scamming%20them%20out%20of%20%248.8%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20June%2C%20an%20additional%20%3Ca%