ss%20the%20victim%20and%20slapped%20her%20when%20she%20spurned%20his%20advances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditional%20Sessions%20Judge%20Sunil%20Gupta%20was%20hearing%20an%20appeal%20filed%20by%20accused%20Sandeep%20Gupta%20against%20his%20conviction%20by%20a%20Mahila%20Court%20on%20February%205%2C%202019%20under%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%20sections%20354%20(assault%20or%20criminal%20force%20to%20a%20woman%20with%20intent%20to%20outrage%20her%20modesty)%20and%20323%20(voluntarily%20causing%20hurt).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20prosecution%20has%20proved%20that%20the%20appellant%20(Gupta)%20has%20used%20criminal%20force%20against%20the%20complainant%20knowing%20that%20he%20will%20thereby%20outrage%20her%20modesty%20by%20trying%20to%20kiss%20her%20and%20also%20voluntarily%20caused%20hurt%20to%20her%20by%20slapping%20her%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20magisterial%20court%20had%20%26quot%3Brightly%20convicted%26quot%3B%20him%20of%20the%20offences%20under%20IPC%20sections%20354%20and%20323.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20dismissed%20the%20defence%20counsel's%20argument%20regarding%20the%20absence%20of%20medical%20evidence%20to%20show%20that%20the%20victim%20was%20beaten%20and%20the%20victim%20not%20getting%20herself%20medically%20examined%20as%20she%20was%20allegedly%20drunk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMere%20slap%20to%20a%20person%20is%20sufficient%20to%20make%20out%20a%20case%20for%20the%20offence%20under%20section%20323%20of%20the%20IPC%E2%80%A6%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSimilarly%2C%20even%20if%20the%20medical%20examination%20of%20the%20complainant%20would%20have%20shown%20that%20she%20was%20drunk%20at%20that%20time%2C%20that%20in%20itself%20would%20not%20have%20been%20of%20any%20consequence%20as%20the%20intoxication%20of%20a%20lady%20does%20not%20give%20licence%20to%20her%20male%20friend%20to%20take%20undue%20advantage%20of%20her%20condition%2C%26quot%3B%