2https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-sets-aside-order-suspending-conviction-of-lakshadweep-mp-mohammed-faizal-asks-kerala-hc-to-decide-afresh-235848%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20bench%20of%20Justices%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20said%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20(NCP)%20leader%20can%20continue%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20have%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20suspension%20of%20conviction%20until%20the%20high%20court%20disposes%20of%20the%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20this%20year%2C%20Faizal%20and%20three%20others%20were%20convicted%20for%C2%A0attempting%20to%20murder%20the%20son-in-law%20of%20a%20Congress%20leader%20during%20the%202009%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%20He%20was%20sentenced%20to%2010%20years%20in%20jail%2C%20which%20meant%20that%20he%20was%20automatically%20disqualified%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20The%20NCP%20leader%20received%20a%20reprieve%20when%20a%20single-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Kerala%20high%20court%20suspended%20his%20conviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20Justice%20Nagarathna-led%20bench%20observed%20that%20while%20suspending%20the%20conviction%20and%20sentence%2C%20the%20high%20court%20%E2%80%9Chad%20not%20considered%20the%20true%20position%20of%20law%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20an%20application%20for%20a%20stay%20on%20conviction%20must%20be%20considered%E2%80%9D.%20The%20top%20court%20said%20that%20the%20HC%E2%80%99s%20thrust%20was%20on%20the%20prospect%20of%20conducting%20a%20fresh%20election%20and%20the%20concomitant%20expenses%20to%20the%20exchequer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20not%20have%20been%20the%20sole%20factor%20to%20suspend%20the%20conviction%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20single-judge%20HC%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Bechu%20Kurian%20Thomas%20had%20suspended%20Faizal%E2%80%99s%20sentence%20soon%20after%20the%20Election%20Commission%20declared%20plans%20to%20hold%20a%20by-poll%20to%20fill%20the%20resultant%20vacancy.%20Justice%20Thomas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Flakshadweep-mp-mohammed-faizal-election-commission-kerala-high-court%5C%22%3Eexpressed%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20%E2%80%9Cassociated%20expenditures%20and%20observed%20that%20the%20newly%20elected%20candidate%20would%20be%20able%20to%20function%20only%20for%20a%20period%20less%20than%20fifteen%20months%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20was%20appealed%20by%20both%20the%20administration%20of%20the%20Union%20Territory%20of%20Lakshadweep%20and%20the%20complainant%20who%20accused%20the%20parliamentarian%20of%20attempting%20to%20murder%20him.%20It%20was%20in%20this%20appeal%20that%20the%20top%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20on%20Tuesday%20was%20delivered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20secretariat%20acted%20swiftly%20to%20disqualify%20his%20membership%20after%20the%20conviction%2C%20it%20was%20only%20restored%20over%20two%20months%20after%20the%20HC%20order%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flok-sabha-lakshadweep-mp-faizal-restored%5C%22%3Ehours%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20to%20hear%20Faizal%E2%80%99s%20appeal%20about%20the%20delay.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692707388000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F14133347%2FUntitled-design-13.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-mohammed-faizal-mp-suspension-set-aside%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20top%20court%20said%20Mohammed%20Faizal%2C%20a%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20leader%2C%20can%20continue%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20have%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20suspension%20of%20conviction%20until%20the%20high%20court%20disposes%20of%20the%20appli