pones-removal-of-jio-financial-services-from-indices-to-august-29-123082200571_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Law%20Raises%20Questions%20About%20Consistency%20With%20Right%20to%20Privacy%20Ruling%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F25143729%2Fdata-protection-1200x600.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%20(DPDPA)%2C%202023%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20passed%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20%E2%80%93%20has%20now%20become%20a%20law.%20It%20received%20presidential%20assent%20on%20August%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20the%20law%20is%20impeded%20by%20several%20fundamental%20flaws%2C%20which%20are%20likely%20to%20prevent%20it%20from%20fulfilling%20the%20purported%20objectives%20that%20were%20sought%20to%20be%20achieved%20when%20it%20was%20being%20drafted%20as%20a%20data%20protection%20and%20privacy%20law.%20More%20importantly%2C%20the%20law%20may%20ultimately%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20tool%20through%20which%20the%20government%20will%20be%20able%20to%20circumvent%20the%20already%20scant%20mechanisms%20that%20are%20available%20to%20individuals%20with%20regard%20to%20their%20ability%20to%20exercise%20informational%20autonomy%20and%20ensure%20the%20privacy%20of%20their%20personal%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20initial%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20was%20prepared%20and%20delivered%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20(MeitY)%20by%20an%20expert%20committee%20headed%20by%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20B.N.%20Srikrishna%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.meity.gov.in%2Fwritereaddata%2Ffiles%2FPersonal_Data_Protection_Bill%2C2018.pdf%5C%22%3E2018.%3C%2Fa%3E%20This%20happened%20after%20a%20year%20of%20deliberations%20and%20changes%20since%20the%20need%20for%20a%20privacy%20law%20was%20articulated%20in%20the%20landmark%202017%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-aadhaar-right-to-privacy%5C%22%3Ejudgment%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgender%2Faadhaar-privacy-judgment-supreme-court-section-377%5C%22%3Eof%20%3Cem%3EJustice%20K.S.%20Puttaswamy%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%20In%20the%20ruling%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20held%20privacy%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right%20protected%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20letter%20and%20spirit%20of%20the%20law%20have%20seen%20several%20deviations%20since%20that%20time.%20However%2C%20the%202018%20draft%20Bill%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20recognised%20the%20importance%20of%20appropriately%20classifying%20data%2C%20affording%20special%20consideration%20to%20protect%20personal%20data%20which%20is%20deemed%20sensitive%20in%20nature.%20The%20most%20recent%20iteration%20of%20the%20law%20however%20does%20not%20make%20a%20distinction%20between%20personal%20data%20and%20sensitive%20personal%20data%2C%20nor%20does%20it%20afford%20any%20additional%20consideration%20to%20adequately%20protect%20such%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fdata-protection-bull-proliferation-digital-india%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20Won%E2%80%99t%20Stop%20Data%20Proliferation%20in%20Digital%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20advantages.%20For%20instance%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20personal%20data%20belonging%20to%20or%20identifying%20children%20will%20have%20to%20be%20classified%20separately%2C%20with%20such%20data%20carrying%20a%20greater%20degree%20of%20security%20and%20privacy.%20The%20law%20also%20seeks%20to%20reduce%20the%20rate%20and%20impact%20of%20data%20breaches%20targeting%20Indian%20businesses.%20The%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20law%2C%20however%2C%20goes%20a%20step%20beyond%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fdata-protection-bill-2023-fine-upto-rs-250-crore-on-entities-for-breaching-data-of-citizens-11691109733488.html%5C%22%3Eimposing%20penalties%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20cases%20where%20data%20is%20breached%20as%20a%20result%20of%20a%20lack%20of%20implementation%20of%20adequate%20security%20controls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20be%20said%20that%20the%20law%20isn%E2%80%99t%20balanced%2C%20because%20it%20provides%20wide%20exemptions%20to%20the%20processing%20of%20personal%20data%20to%20the%20government.%20For%20instance%2C%20data%20can%20be%20processed%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20interest%20of%20prevention%2C%20detection%2C%20investigation%20or%20prosecution%20of%20any%20offence%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%20These%20kinds%20of%20exemptions%20are%20dangerous%20as%20they%20stand%20to%20legitimise%20widespread%20and%20unwarranted%20collection%20of%20data%20under%20the%20guise%20that%20such%20collection%20and%20processing%20may%20ultimately%20be%20useful%20for%20preventing%20or%20deterring%20a%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20theory%2C%20any%20data%20belonging%20to%20any%20person%2C%20at%20any%20time%2C%20may%20potentially%20be%20useful%20in%20the%20future%20indefinitely%20for%20the%20prevention%20or%20detection%20of%20a%20crime%2C%20retrospectively%20or%20otherwise.%20In%20that%20light%2C%20unchecked%20and%20surreptitious%20government%20surveillance%20is%20not%20only%20still%20a%20risk%20with%20the%20DPDPA%2C%20but%20such%20surveillance%20now%20has%20legal%20backing%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecurity%20agencies%20will%20have%20significant%20authority%20to%20collect%20and%20retain%20any%20data%20whatsoever%2C%20as%20is%20typically%20the%20case%20with%20exemptions%20relating%20to%20the%20maintenance%20of%20sovereignty%2C%20integrity%2C%20security%20of%20the%20state%2C%20preservation%20of%20public%20order%2C%20prevention%20of%20offences%2C%20and%20incitement%20to%20commit%20offences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20also%20exempts%20processing%20of%20personal%20data%20held%20outside%20of%20India.%20The%20government%20is%20also%20exempt%20from%20being%20required%20to%20delete%20any%20data%20that%20it%20possesses%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20purpose%20it%20may%20have%20been%20collected%20for%2C%20on%20the%20request%20of%20an%20individual%2C%20or%20by%20way%20of%20a%20prescribed%20data%20retention%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20is%20not%20bound%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fuk.practicallaw.thomsonreuters.com%2FGlossary%2FUKPracticalLaw%2FI1a11102e5ea511e89bf199c0ee06c731%3FtransitionType%3DDefault%26contextData%3D(sc.Default)%26firstPage%3Dtrue%5C%22%3Epurpose%20limitations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20allowing%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edata%20collected%20for%20one%20specified%20purpose%20be%20used%20for%20a%20new%2C%20incompatible%20purpose%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20which%20stands%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20regulations%20imposed%20on%20businesses.%20However%2C%20certain%20types%20of%20data%2C%20particularly%20sensitive%20personal%20data%2C%20would%20legitimately%20warrant%20prescribed%20retention%20periods.%20It%E2%80%99s%20worth%20noting%20that%20the%20law%20does%20not%20prioritise%20one%20category%20of%20data%20over%20another%2C%20except%20in%20cases%20involving%20data%20related%20to%20or%20concerning%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fdigital-personal-data-protection-bill-adverse-impact-press-freedom-editors-guild%5C%22%3EDigital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20Could%20Have%20Adverse%20Impact%20on%20Press%20Freedom%2C%20Say%20Editors%20Guild%20and%20Digipub%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20exemptions%20for%20the%20government%20relate%20to%20data%20deemed%20%E2%80%9Cnecessary%20for%20research%2C%20archiving%20or%20statistical%20purposes%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%E2%80%9D%20as%20long%20as%20such%20data%20is%20not%20used%20to%20make%20a%20decision%20for%20the%20persons%20whom%20the%20data%20identifies.%20This%20may%20seem%20an%20agreeable%20exemption%20when%20compared%20to%20the%20ones%20described%20above%2C%20but%20exemptions%20for%20purposes%20such%20as%20research%20or%20archival%20are%20overly%20broad%2C%20and%20may%20still%20violate%20the%20constitutional%20right%20to%20privacy%20of%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20summation%2C%20the%20Act%20conflates%20the%20concept%20of%20informational%20privacy%20and%20leaves%20much%20to%20be%20desired%20as%20it%20substitutes%20information%20security%20with%20the%20ability%20of%20an%20individual%20to%20exercise%20autonomy%20over%20the%20privacy%20of%20their%20data.%20The%20enactment%20of%20the%20DPDPA%20in%20this%20state%20appears%20to%20deviate%20from%20the%20original%20vision%20of%20what%20the%20law%20could%20have%20been%2C%20especially%20since%20the%20need%20for%20such%20legislation%20was%20first%20articulated%20in%20the%20Right%20to%20Privacy%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKaran%20Saini%20is%20a%20Delhi-based%20security%20researcher%20with%20Infosec%20Clinic.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692700244000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F25143729%2Fdata-protection-1200x600.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdigital-personal-data-protection-law-raises-questions-about-consistency-with-right-to-privacy-ruling%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20appears%20that%20the%20law%20is%20impeded%20by%20several%20fundamental%20flaws%2C%20which%20are%20likely%20to%20prevent%20it%20from%20fulfilling%20the%20purported%20objectives%20that%20were%20sought%20to%20be%20achieved%20when%20it%20was%20being%20drafted%20as%20a%20data%20protection%20and%20privacy%20law.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdigital-personal-data-protection-law-raises-questions-about-consistency-with-right-to-privacy-ruling%22%2