%7B%22title%22%3A%22Intelligence%20Bureau%20at%20Ashoka%20University%2C%20Wants%20to%20Probe%20%E2%80%98Democratic%20Backsliding%E2%80%99%20Paper%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F22152611%2FScreenshot-2023-08-22-at-3.25.41-PM.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20a%20development%20with%20ominous%20implications%20for%20academic%20freedom%20in%20India%2C%20the%20Intelligence%20Bureau%20has%20begun%20looking%C2%A0%20into%20the%20scholarly%20paper%20by%20a%20former%20Ashoka%20University%20professor%20on%20%E2%80%98Democratic%20Backsliding%20in%20the%20World%E2%80%99s%20Largest%20Democracy%E2%80%99%20and%20is%20seeking%20to%20interview%20the%20author%20and%20faculty%20members%20of%20the%20economics%20department%20on%20the%20subject.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIB%20officials%20visited%20the%20private%20university%20on%20Monday%20armed%20with%20newspaper%20cuttings%20seeking%20to%20meet%20the%20author%20of%20the%20paper%2C%20Sabyasachi%20Das%2C%20who%20is%20currently%20in%20Pune.%20A%20suggestion%20that%20other%20members%20of%20the%20faculty%20meet%20with%20them%20to%20discuss%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20paper%20found%20no%20takers%20as%20the%20officials%20refused%20to%20convey%20their%20request%20for%20information%20in%20writing.%20They%20then%20left%20after%20saying%20they%20would%20return%20to%20the%20campus%20again%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20some%20faculty%20members%20were%20advised%20to%20be%20ready%20to%20field%20questions%20from%20the%20IB%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20%E2%80%98behind%20the%20scenes%E2%80%99%20player%2C%20the%20IB%20does%20not%20have%20powers%20that%20the%20police%20and%20investigative%20agencies%20have%20to%20formally%20interrogate%20anyone%20or%20even%20arrest.%20The%20role%20it%20plays%20through%20its%20%E2%80%98investigations%E2%80%99%20is%20to%20%E2%80%98develop%20intelligence%E2%80%99%20that%20other%20agencies%20then%20get%20to%20act%20upon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDas%E2%80%99s%20paper%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4512936%5C%22%3Epublished%20online%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20uses%20advanced%20econometric%20techniques%20to%20generate%20estimates%20of%20how%20many%20of%20the%20marginal%20seats%20in%20the%202019%20general%20election%20that%20the%20BJP%20won%20might%20have%20been%20due%20to%20some%20form%20of%20%E2%80%98manipulation%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20set%20off%20a%20political%20controversy%2C%20with%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20leaders%20denouncing%20Das%E2%80%99s%20research.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learned%20that%20some%20of%20the%20businessmen%20who%20invested%20in%20Ashoka%20and%20sit%20on%20its%20board%20received%20angry%20calls%20from%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%20as%20well%20as%20from%20the%20Union%20education%20minister%2C%20in%20which%20the%20scholar%E2%80%99s%20motives%20were%20questioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Haryana-based%20Ashoka%20University%20has%20often%20played%20host%20to%20%E2%80%98sleuths%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20local%20Intelligence%20Bureau%20(LIB)%20%E2%80%93%20who%20attend%20seminars%20and%20events%20to%20take%20notes%20when%20the%20topic%20is%20even%20vaguely%20political%20%E2%80%93%20this%20is%20the%20first%20time%20the%20IB%20has%20deputed%20officers%20from%20its%20headquarters%20to%20visit%20the%20Sonepat%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20familiar%20with%20the%20working%20of%20the%20IB%20say%20that%20a%20standard%20part%20of%20the%20agency%E2%80%99s%20playbook%20is%20to%20try%20and%20establish%20whether%20a%20person%20of%20interest%20is%20acting%20at%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbehest%E2%80%9D%20of%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IB%E2%80%99s%20interest%20in%20Das%20and%20his%20paper%20comes%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20unconfirmed%20reports%20that%20the%20university%20is%20considering%20inviting%20the%20young%20economist%20%E2%80%93%20who%20resigned%20when%20Ashoka%20publicly%20distanced%20itself%20from%20his%20work%20%E2%80%93%20to%20rejoin%20the%20faculty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECoincidentally%2C%20Ashoka%20University%E2%80%99s%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%20license%20is%20coming%20up%20for%20renewal%20in%20September%202023.%20The%20renewal%20of%20FCRA%20licenses%20has%20been%20a%20tool%20often%20used%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20to%20go%20after%20institutions%20not%20fully%20aligned%20with%20the%20government%20or%20the%20BJP%20and%20its%20affiliated%20bodies.%20Sources%20say%20that%20preparation%20of%20reports%20by%20intelligence%20sources%20is%20often%20done%2C%20especially%20in%20matters%20where%20the%20MHA%20suspects%20the%20absence%20of%20complete%20alignment%20with%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20ideas%20or%20objectives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshoka%20is%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20growing%20concerns%20about%20academic%20freedom%20after%20Das%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fauthor-of-paper-on-possible-manipulation-in-2019-polls-quits-ashoka-university%5C%22%3Eresigned%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4512936%5C%22%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Senior%20economics%20professor%20Pulapre%20Balakrishnan%20resigned%20soon%20after%2C%20citing%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20handling%20of%20the%20controversy.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20resigned%20my%20position%20based%20on%20my%20belief%20that%20there%20was%20a%20grave%20error%20of%20judgment%20in%20the%20response%20to%20the%20attention%20received%20by%20Das%E2%80%99s%20paper%20on%20social%20media.%20Academic%20freedom%20was%20violated%20in%20the%20response%2C%20and%20it%20would%20be%20unconscionable%20for%20me%20to%20remain%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Facademic-freedom-was-violated-economist-pulapre-balakrishnan-on-quitting-ashoka-university%2Fcid%2F1960164%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20his%20resignation%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20economics%20departments%20and%20other%20faculty%20members%20have%20issued%20statements%20in%20solidarity%20with%20Das%2C%20and%20calling%20upon%20the%20university%20administration%20to%20take%20steps%20to%20bring%20the%20economist%20back%20and%20provide%20guarantees%20that%20the%20academic%20freedom%20of%20faculty%20and%20students%20will%20be%20respected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20contacted%20the%20Ashoka%20University%20administration%20for%20a%20formal%20statement%20on%20the%20Intelligence%20Bureau%E2%80%99s%20visit%20and%20this%20story%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20we%20hear%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20This%20story%20was%20updated%20at%201848%20to%20add%20additional%20details.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692699532000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F22152611%2FScreenshot-2023-08-22-at-3.25.41-PM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fintelligence-bureau-at-ashoka-university-wants-to-probe-democratic-backsliding-paper%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22IB%20officials%20arrived%20Monday%20to%20speak%20to%20former%20faculty%20member%20Sabyasachi%20Das%2C%20and%20unsuccessfully%20tried%20to%20speak%20to%20others%20from%20the%20economics%20department%20after%20learning%20he%20was%20not%20on%20campus.%20A%20second%20visit%20was%20then%20set%20for%20Tuesday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A281%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fintelligence-bureau-at-ashoka-university-wants-to-probe-democratic-backsliding-paper%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Manipur%3A%20SC-Appointed%20Panel%20Calls%20for%20Reconstruction%20of%20Lost%20Documents%2C%20Compensation%20Scheme%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F11142639%2FUntitled-design-1-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20appointed%20committee%20that%20is%20looking%20into%20the%20violence%20in%20Manipur%20has%20highlighted%20the%20recovery%20and%20reconstruction%20of%20documents%20lost%20in%20arson%20and%20gunfire%20as%20the%20first%20step%2C%20followed%20by%20just%20compensation%20rules%20and%20appointment%20of%20domain%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20comprises%20three%20retired%20women%20who%20were%20judges%20at%20high%20courts.%20It%20is%20headed%20by%20former%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20high%20court%20Chief%20Justice%20Gita%20Mittal%20and%20also%20has%20Justices%20Shalini%20Phansalkar%20Joshi%20and%20Asha%20Menon.%20This%20committee%20has%20submitted%20three%20reports%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fmanipur-violence-judges-committee-submit-reports-to-supreme-court-235711%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20CJI%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20Justice%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%2C%20and%20Justice%20Manoj%20Misra%20directed%20for%20the%20reports%20to%20be%20circulated%20to%20the%20counsels%20and%20asked%20them%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20proposed%20suggestions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20of%20the%20three%20reports%20submitted%20by%20the%20committee%20highlights%20the%20loss%20of%20essential%20documentation%20of%20the%20residents%20of%20Manipur%20who%20have%20been%20dishoused%2C%E2%80%9D%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20said%20after%20looking%20at%20the%20report%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fmanipur-violence-supreme-court-to-pass-orders-on-august-25-to-facilitate-proper-functioning-of-justice-mittal-panel%2Farticle67218800.ece%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20suggested%20that%20a%20nodal%20officer%20be%20appointed%20to%20head%20the%20process%20of%20reconstructing%20these%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20documents%20lost%20are%20Aadhaar%20cards%2C%20which%20are%20tied%20to%20welfare%20scheme%20benefits%20and%20also%20bank%20accounts%2C%20the%20CJI%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20report%20has%20highlighted%20that%20the%20compensation%20scheme%20for%20victims%20in%20Manipur%20needs%20to%20be%20improved%20and%20updated%20with%20the%20NALSA%20scheme%20in%20mind%2C%20reports%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20Manipur%20compensation%20scheme%20keeps%20victims%20who%20have%20benefitted%20from%20other%20schemes%20out%20of%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20report%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20proposed%20the%20appointment%20of%20domain%20experts%20for%20administrative%20directions.%20The%20bench%20noted%20also%20that%20certain%20procedural%20directions%20were%20required%20in%20the%20matter%20to%20pay%20for%20expenses%20including%20infrastructure.%20It%20asked%20advocate%20Vrinda%20Grover%20to%20collate%20relevant%20suggestions%20and%20share%20them%20with%20the%20Advocate%20General%20of%20Manipur%20later%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692698857000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F11142639%2FUntitled-design-1-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmanipur-supreme-court-gita-mittal-committee-report-documents-compensation%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'The%20first%20of%20the%20three%20reports%20submitted%20by%20the%20committee%20highlights%20the%20loss%20of%20essential%20documentation%20of%20the%20residents%20of%20Manipur%20who%20have%20been%20dishoused...'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmanipur-supreme-court-gita-mittal-committee-report-documents-compensatio