0from%20further%20investigation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fed-cannot-be-a-law-unto-itself-supreme-court-says%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%20%7C%20'Modi%20Govt's%20EC%20Bill%20Undermines%20Its%20Independence%2C%20Should%20Be%20Struck%20Down%20if%20Passed'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F22143854%2FKT-22-Aug.00_25_18_25.Still006.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20scholar%20Gautam%20Bhatia%20says%20the%20controversy%20and%20debate%20surrounding%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20Bill%20creating%20a%20mechanism%20for%20the%20selection%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20%E2%80%9Cmisses%20the%20point%E2%80%9D.%20This%20Bill%20was%20tabled%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20the%20last%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhatia%20says%20the%20key%20concern%20is%20not%20whether%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20is%20part%20of%20the%20panel%20that%20appoints%20the%20CEC%20and%20EC%20but%20that%20the%20process%20must%20be%20independent%20of%20the%20government%20and%20not%20in%20any%20way%20dominated%20by%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F_BbrnLupDm4%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2020-minute%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Bhatia%20explains%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20key%20concern%20in%20the%20Anoop%20Baranwal%20case%20was%20that%20the%20mechanism%20to%20appoint%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20must%20secure%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission.%20That%20can%20only%20be%20done%20by%20a%20non-partisan%20or%20multi-partisan%20appointment%20mechanism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20not%20happen%20if%20the%20mechanism%20is%20dominated%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20another%20minister%20appointed%20by%20the%20PM.%20Equally%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20essential%20that%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20should%20be%20part%20of%20the%20mechanism.%20That%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20detail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20debate%20in%20India%20has%20so%20far%20focused%20on%20the%20exclusion%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20from%20the%20appointment%20mechanism%20rather%20than%20on%20the%20need%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20mechanism%20is%20independent%20of%20the%20government%20and%20not%20influenced%20by%20it.%20Only%20then%20can%20the%20mechanism%20ensure%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhatia%20discusses%20what%20happens%20in%20other%20major%20parliamentary%20democracies%20and%20whether%20the%20appointment%20of%20a%20Search%20Committee%20to%20put%20forward%20a%20panel%20of%20five%20candidates%20to%20the%20selection%20committee%20headed%20by%20the%20PM%20alleviates%20the%20concerns%20that%20have%20been%20raised.%20He%20discusses%20two%20points%20made%20by%20former%20CEC%20S.%20Y.%20Quraishi.%20First%2C%20that%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20in%20the%20appointing%20panel%20could%20create%20problems%20if%20there%20is%20a%20challenge%20because%20it%20would%20then%20automatically%20go%20to%20him%20and%20create%20a%20conflict%20of%20interest.%20Second%2C%20if%20the%20government%20refuses%20to%20change%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20appointing%20panel%20should%20the%20selection%20be%20unanimous%20rather%20than%20based%20on%20majority%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhatia%20discusses%20the%20possibility%20of%20this%20Bill%2C%20if%20it%20is%20passed%2C%20being%20struck%20down%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20He%20also%20discusses%20the%20need%20for%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20act%20expeditiously%20if%20there%20is%20a%20challenge%20rather%20than%20delay%20matters%20for%20years%2C%20as%20happened%20with%20Article%20370%2C%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20Bhatia%20discusses%20the%20political%20morality%20of%20a%20government%20attempting%20to%20blatantly%20defy%20the%20spirit%20of%20democracy%20by%20dominating%20the%20appointing%20panel%20for%20CECs%20and%20ECs.%20What%20does%20this%20reveal%20of%20the%20attitude%20of%20the%20PM%20and%20his%20government%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20fair%20play%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWatch%20the%20full%20interview%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D_BbrnLupDm4%26ab_channel%3DTheWire%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692695747000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F22143854%2FKT-22-Aug.00_25_18_25.Still006.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvideo-karan-thapar-election-commission-gautam-bhatia%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Legal%20scholar%20Gautam%20Bhatia%20says%20the%20key%20concern%20is%20not%20whether%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20is%20part%20of%20the%20panel%20that%20appoints%20the%20CEC%20and%20EC%20but%20that%20the%20process%20must%20be%20independent%20of%20the%20government.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvideo-karan-thapar-election-commission-gautam-bhatia%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Children%20and%20teachers%20trapped%20in%20chairlift%20dangling%20274m%20above%20Pakistan%20canyon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692694920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F08%2F1600x900%2Fskynews-pakistan-cable-car_6259267.jpg%3F20230822151042%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fs